HEADWORD: Propensity
<hw>Pro*pen"si*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Propensities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The quality or state
of being propense; natural inclination; disposition to do good or evil;
bias; bent; tendency.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>propensity</xex> to utter
blasphemy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Disposition; bias; inclination; proclivity;
proneness; bent; tendency.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propenyl</ent>⟦br⟧
